# RuneForged Git Workflow Rules

## Workflow
- Assume work should happen in a feature branch, not directly on main.
- Make reviewable diffs.
- Prefer one coherent change per commit.

## When making changes
- Summarize which files were touched and why.
- If a task is risky, suggest a commit checkpoint before the next step.
- Do not propose broad cleanup commits unless explicitly asked.

## Testing mindset
- After code changes, suggest concrete manual test steps in Godot.
- For gameplay changes, include likely edge cases.
- For save, inventory, and UI changes, include regression checks.